genesis (0.0.1-2) hardy; urgency=low

  * Rename the package to genesis.
  * Remove gnome-vfs-2 dependency, using inotify monitering directories instead.
  * Add interface to send back category name list to users.
  * Add interface to return an application list by a specified category.
  * Remove gnome-vfs-2 and gconf package checking.
  * Clean up source package.
  * Create genesis.h for users to easily use genesis.
  * Remove fs-monitor from controller, fs monitoring will be done in daemon.
  * Remove fs-monitor-test accordingly.
  * Rename libgenesis.pc to genesis.pc.
  * Install header files to /usr/include/genesis.
  * Simplify getting next event from inotify file descriptor.
  * Do not remove extension from application icon.
  * Do not free dirent structure returned from readdir.
  * Modified to provide unfiltered category information.

 -- Horace Li <horace.li@intel.com>  Fri, 25 Jul 2008 16:09:50 +0800

